{
  "stem": "428.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lot of people there was older, they was in the camps, you couldn't no more to walk to work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you couldn't walk to work, couldn't walk to work so you're not-- they don't need you there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They shot you for nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it's a lot of things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, when I-- oh, yeah, in that camp, in the [INAUDIBLE], it used to be-- they used to-- you used to go 6 o'clock in the morning to work, so they take you out from the-- from the camp 5 o'clock, stay outside.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], and it's snow and everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a Jewish guy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a lot of Jews they was worse than SS.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some of them, they were-- This was the Jewish police?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Jewish-- no, he was a block barber.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He used to-- you know what, he was a barber.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you have hair in the middle, they make a line like this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They call it-- the call it a [NON-ENGLISH] promenade.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That you should not run away, that they should know right away that you are a--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he used to come to people in the morning, so you stay-- you have to stay straight.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was cold so I stand like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he kicked me in the stomach, and he tells me of Polish language, [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe would you straighten out?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I straighten out and I told him-- his name was Marian.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I told him, Marian, that war is not going to be forever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm going to live through that-- through that hell, and I catch you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And God help, I was in Germany already after the war in Bamberg.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was a shul there, and we used to come together.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
